Bethesda unit.entity: biologic activity of factor VIII inhibitor

anti factor Xa unit.entity: biologic activity of factor Xa inhibitor (heparin)

index of reactivity (allergen).entity: amount of an allergen callibrated through in-vivo testing using the Stallergenes® method

bioequivalent allergen unit.entity: amount of an allergen callibrated through in-vivo testing based on the ID50EAL method of (intradermal dilution for 50mm sum of erythema diameters

allergy unit.entity: procedure defined amount of an allergen using some reference standard

protein nitrogen unit (allergen testing).entity: procedure defined amount of a protein substance

limit of flocculation.entity: procedure defined amount of an antigen substance

D-antigen unit (polio).entity: procedure defined amount of a poliomyelitis d-antigen substance

fibrinogen equivalent units.entity: amount of fibrinogen broken down into the measured d-dimers
